00:40.387 --> 00:42.093
José. There you go, my friend.

00:42.096 --> 00:44.222
Merry Christmas to you and your family.

00:44.224 --> 00:45.557
All the best, now.

00:45.559 --> 00:47.059
What is this? Oh, Benjamin.

00:47.061 --> 00:50.062
Boy. Here you go, Benjamin, son.

00:50.064 --> 00:52.164
Best to you, now. Merry Christmas.

00:52.166 --> 00:54.899
All the best. I think that's it.

00:59.706 --> 01:02.441
Whoo!

01:02.443 --> 01:05.777
May I have your attention
for a moment, please?

01:05.779 --> 01:07.912
Thank you all for coming,

01:07.914 --> 01:11.039
and a very, very merry
Christmas to you all.

01:11.042 --> 01:14.511
We're so honored to have you here.

01:14.514 --> 01:17.381
I'm...

01:17.384 --> 01:22.521
I'm feeling especially
grateful in this moment.

01:22.524 --> 01:24.895
My boy Pete is home.

01:26.733 --> 01:28.796
I missed him every day,

01:28.799 --> 01:31.466
despite knowing how
bravely he was fighting

01:31.469 --> 01:33.976
those bastards who sought us harm.

01:35.982 --> 01:39.116
How dark those times
must have been for him...

01:39.119 --> 01:42.787
To be so far from his
family who loves him.

01:42.790 --> 01:44.703
Give applause for my son...

01:44.706 --> 01:47.641
...a true Texas hero.

01:47.644 --> 01:49.886
- Hear, hear!
- Yeah.

01:52.157 --> 01:54.424
Come on, now! Let's go!

02:02.234 --> 02:05.265
There are three warlords
and God knows how much chaos

02:05.268 --> 02:07.730
between here and Tampico.

02:07.733 --> 02:11.007
Now, once we get you down
there, it's gonna be better.

02:11.009 --> 02:14.144
You'll be with your... your family.

02:14.146 --> 02:18.147
They're second cousins.
They've never met me.

02:18.149 --> 02:20.023
If you have a better idea...

02:20.026 --> 02:21.526
I don't.

02:21.529 --> 02:24.196
We need the money to travel.

02:26.436 --> 02:27.935
For food.

02:30.074 --> 02:32.342
You keep saying "we."

02:38.619 --> 02:40.770
What are you doing?

02:45.376 --> 02:47.218
I'm not going back.

02:47.221 --> 02:50.021
I've decided.

02:50.024 --> 02:55.294
Do you really think we're
gonna take a train somewhere?

02:55.297 --> 02:57.798
And what?

02:57.801 --> 03:00.301
Get married? Have children?

03:00.304 --> 03:02.872
That ain't what I'm saying.

03:02.875 --> 03:06.476
Then what?

03:06.479 --> 03:08.379
Do you want to be forgiven?

03:10.485 --> 03:13.419
No.

03:13.422 --> 03:17.224
I don't care about you.

03:17.227 --> 03:20.361
I don't need your ring.

03:20.364 --> 03:25.054
The only thing I needed from
you was to stop your father.

03:25.057 --> 03:26.648
And you couldn't.

03:28.184 --> 03:30.518
- My family was counting on you.
- Shh!

03:30.520 --> 03:32.386
- Shh, shh!
- And you couldn't.

03:32.388 --> 03:34.722
It's a war zone. You're
drawing attention.

03:34.724 --> 03:36.546
Okay. Shh, shh.

03:36.549 --> 03:38.750
Hold it together.

03:38.753 --> 03:41.087
We'll get through this.

03:44.394 --> 03:46.027
It's okay.

03:48.867 --> 03:50.566
You ruined my life.

