28:08.440 --> 28:10.440
Hey, brother.

28:13.311 --> 28:17.080
It's special, so I wanted it to be last.

28:17.082 --> 28:18.981
- Wow.
- Open it.

28:21.186 --> 28:23.619
Been saving it for the right time.

28:26.591 --> 28:27.923
That's a handsome gun.

28:27.925 --> 28:29.024
It's engraved.

28:32.330 --> 28:33.496
Thank you.

28:33.498 --> 28:35.465
The old man got you down?

28:37.969 --> 28:40.928
Finn do you know about his plans

28:40.931 --> 28:42.370
for the oil business?

28:42.372 --> 28:43.681
Long term?

28:43.684 --> 28:45.840
Who do you think comes
up with those plans,

28:45.842 --> 28:47.976
writes 'em down and makes 'em happen?

28:47.978 --> 28:49.344
So you know.

28:49.346 --> 28:50.778
About?

28:50.780 --> 28:54.682
Him wanting me to take over. Eventually.

28:54.684 --> 28:56.951
Of course.

28:59.173 --> 29:01.490
Governor, though.
That's really something.

29:01.492 --> 29:04.159
Mm-hmm.

29:04.161 --> 29:08.029
Well, that's a long ways off to be sure.

29:08.031 --> 29:10.398
I wonder if you'll still
talk to us little people.

29:13.136 --> 29:14.392
I'll see... see to it

29:14.395 --> 29:17.029
you have a desk in
the Governor's Mansion,

29:17.032 --> 29:20.473
just like mine, but slightly smaller.

29:21.677 --> 29:23.142
Excuse me.

29:43.433 --> 29:45.700
People seemed to enjoy themselves.

29:49.606 --> 29:51.872
You want one?

29:51.874 --> 29:54.875
No, I'm good.

29:54.877 --> 29:57.312
Suit yourself.

29:57.314 --> 29:59.447
How long is it gonna take, Sal?

30:01.184 --> 30:03.218
For what?

30:03.220 --> 30:06.521
You to consider forgiving
me just a little bit.

30:08.658 --> 30:11.058
Years.

30:11.060 --> 30:12.659
Maybe.

30:12.661 --> 30:16.030
I mean, maybe it takes forever.

30:16.032 --> 30:18.465
Maybe I just keep you standing there,

30:18.467 --> 30:21.802
waiting, not knowing.

30:25.407 --> 30:26.858
Damn it!

30:28.310 --> 30:30.577
- C'mon.
- Is it bleeding bad?

30:30.579 --> 30:32.579
Let me see.

30:32.581 --> 30:35.149
Not too bad. Not too bad.

30:37.086 --> 30:39.053
It's gonna be all right.

30:40.556 --> 30:43.523
I see you don't wear your ring.

30:43.525 --> 30:46.693
Yeah, they took it in jail.

30:46.695 --> 30:48.228
I need to get a new one.

30:52.501 --> 30:54.668
I'll wait.

30:54.670 --> 30:56.336
However long.

31:02.444 --> 31:06.212
Was I really that bad?

31:06.214 --> 31:09.616
Oh, Sal.

31:09.618 --> 31:12.185
There isn't a bad thing about you.

31:18.927 --> 31:21.360
I guess he told you.

31:21.362 --> 31:22.710
You knew he would.

31:22.713 --> 31:25.468
Oh, I've got great things
in store for you, my son.

31:25.471 --> 31:26.913
But not the family business.

31:26.916 --> 31:28.866
Oh, you can be part of
this as much as anyone.

31:28.869 --> 31:31.537
Ah. Just not the face to the public.

31:31.539 --> 31:34.407
You belong in Austin.
Where the real power is.

31:34.409 --> 31:35.941
And one of these days, you'll be sitting

31:35.943 --> 31:37.880
- in the Governor's mansion...
- Governor's mansion.

31:37.882 --> 31:39.578
Yeah. Right.

31:39.580 --> 31:41.213
That's a pipe dream, and you know it.

31:41.215 --> 31:44.383
Oh, we can get that done. Believe me.

31:46.721 --> 31:49.988
You couldn't even tell
me this to my face.

31:49.990 --> 31:52.758
- Is it because...
- Of course not.

31:52.760 --> 31:54.259
You want to batch up with a friend,

31:54.261 --> 31:56.227
that's your business,

31:56.229 --> 31:57.762
as long as you're discreet.

31:57.764 --> 32:00.398
Then why?

32:02.101 --> 32:07.405
As much as it drives me
crazy, Pete sticks to his guns.

32:07.407 --> 32:10.908
You're a good son.

32:10.910 --> 32:13.345
You do what you're told.

32:13.347 --> 32:17.382
But in this business, you
got to be your own man.

32:17.384 --> 32:20.885
You're holding my loyalty against me?

32:20.887 --> 32:23.521
Your strengths lie elsewhere.

32:23.523 --> 32:25.457
What about what I want?

32:25.459 --> 32:26.958
Oh.

32:26.960 --> 32:29.360
Everyone's got their part to play.

32:41.374 --> 32:43.769
- Hey, Finn. You leaving?
- Yeah.

32:43.772 --> 32:45.376
The old man is sending me to Austin.

32:45.378 --> 32:47.066
- Let me walk you out.
- Nah, I'm fine.

32:47.069 --> 32:48.912
Hey, Finn.

32:48.914 --> 32:51.382
I know you're not okay
with his plan for us.

32:51.384 --> 32:53.216
It's you who should be runnin' it.

32:53.218 --> 32:55.419
Damn right it should be.

32:57.356 --> 32:59.556
I gotta hand it to you, brother.

32:59.558 --> 33:01.992
I don't know what you do,

33:01.994 --> 33:05.661
but you cast a real spell
over that old son of a bitch.

33:25.784 --> 33:27.884
I'm tired of being chased.

33:32.123 --> 33:34.757
Maybe it doesn't have to be like this.

33:37.280 --> 33:42.530
_

33:42.533 --> 33:44.533
They still fight by their side.

33:46.427 --> 33:48.102
_

33:48.105 --> 33:49.575
Their mean women.

33:51.112 --> 33:53.057
_

33:53.060 --> 33:55.277
It could work.

33:55.279 --> 33:57.779
What are you talking about?

33:59.650 --> 34:03.718
Comanches should join
together as one band

34:03.720 --> 34:06.388
and kill all the whites.

34:06.390 --> 34:09.291
There are thousands
and thousands of whites.

34:10.893 --> 34:12.793
Why do they keep coming after us?

34:12.795 --> 34:15.897
'Cause they want the land.

34:15.899 --> 34:18.333
They'll have to kill
all of us to get it.

34:18.335 --> 34:20.835
But I think we can kill them first.

34:20.837 --> 34:22.670
We can't.

34:24.639 --> 34:30.978
Well, if we can't beat all the whites,

34:30.981 --> 34:33.181
maybe we could live with them.

34:33.183 --> 34:34.482
You and me?

34:35.818 --> 34:38.453
What? I could wear a dress.

34:38.455 --> 34:39.853
You'd look like a pea hen.

34:39.856 --> 34:41.130
You looked like a baby deer...

34:41.132 --> 34:43.456
_

34:46.161 --> 34:48.795
I could steal a dress,

34:48.797 --> 34:51.797
and you could take me
to visit the white world.

34:51.800 --> 34:54.101
I speak the language.

34:54.103 --> 34:56.268
Though maybe I won't say nothing.

34:56.271 --> 35:01.841
I'll just let you walk me
around the village by your side.

35:01.843 --> 35:04.544
I want to see people's faces.

35:06.815 --> 35:09.516
Why are you talkin' about the
white world all of a sudden?

35:12.888 --> 35:17.957
Hey. I'm happy here.

35:17.959 --> 35:19.192
With you.

35:26.201 --> 35:28.200
Good.

35:31.339 --> 35:34.140
That's what I wanted you to say.

35:35.176 --> 35:37.644
'Cause we're having a baby.

35:37.646 --> 35:40.547
What?

35:40.549 --> 35:42.481
When?

35:42.483 --> 35:43.983
In the spring.

35:45.420 --> 35:47.353
I'm gonna be a father?

35:51.359 --> 35:52.926
You better get ready.

35:52.928 --> 35:54.575
I'm ready to make another one right now.

35:55.814 --> 35:57.229
Sleep...

35:59.991 --> 36:01.147
_

36:07.240 --> 36:08.955
Well, shit.

36:24.960 --> 36:27.861
You thought about meeting
my Cherokee next week?

36:29.665 --> 36:31.431
- Maybe.
- Mm.

36:31.433 --> 36:35.669
You willing to take a
step in my direction first?

36:36.939 --> 36:38.672
Hmm.

36:38.674 --> 36:40.507
What do you have in mind?

36:46.148 --> 36:47.781
We are closed!

36:49.952 --> 36:52.029
I said we are closed!

36:53.621 --> 36:56.022
Oh. Colonel.

36:56.025 --> 36:58.625
I had no idea it was you.

36:58.627 --> 36:59.959
- Mm.
- Come on in.

36:59.961 --> 37:02.328
Apologies for my late arrival.

37:02.330 --> 37:05.398
For you, the door is always open.

37:10.505 --> 37:13.506
I appreciate you greatly as an employee,

37:13.508 --> 37:18.978
but more important than that,
as a good and true friend.

37:21.183 --> 37:23.883
Warms my heart, Colonel.

37:23.885 --> 37:25.851
It's been quite a Christmas.

37:25.853 --> 37:28.254
Yeah, that it has.

37:28.256 --> 37:31.891
I appreciate everything
you've done for my family.

37:31.893 --> 37:34.151
You've labored hard and well.

37:34.154 --> 37:37.028
Oh, I come from working stock.

37:37.030 --> 37:38.497
Idle and hands and all.

37:38.499 --> 37:41.971
You know, I've been thinking...

37:44.037 --> 37:46.738
...you should take some time off.

37:46.740 --> 37:49.374
Time off.

37:49.376 --> 37:51.943
Hell, I wouldn't even
know what to do with that.

37:51.945 --> 37:54.513
Oh, but you could travel to Georgia,

37:54.515 --> 37:57.416
see that little lady you've
been corresponding with.

37:57.418 --> 37:59.017
I'll cover your travel.

38:00.387 --> 38:05.090
I must confess, sir, I'm confused.

38:05.092 --> 38:06.891
Well, I'll keep paying you, of course,

38:06.893 --> 38:12.129
and you can consider the
loan on this bar forgiven.

38:12.131 --> 38:13.297
It's yours...

38:13.299 --> 38:16.367
outright.

38:19.972 --> 38:22.373
You're trying to get rid of me.

38:22.375 --> 38:26.043
Oh, it's not forever.

38:26.045 --> 38:31.048
Down the line when
things cool off a bit,

38:31.050 --> 38:34.151
you'll be back in the
thick of it with us.

38:34.153 --> 38:38.389
Colonel, I'm loyal.

38:40.793 --> 38:43.794
I've stood by your side.

38:43.796 --> 38:47.664
And I've sullied my hands
on many a misadventure

38:47.666 --> 38:51.468
so that you would not
have to tarnish your own.

38:51.470 --> 38:55.171
I value your loyalty greatly.

38:55.173 --> 39:00.277
Well, then let me be blunt.

39:00.279 --> 39:02.679
You need me now.

39:02.681 --> 39:06.264
You don't want to cut me
loose with enemies at the gate.

39:08.487 --> 39:11.621
The decision's been made.

39:11.623 --> 39:14.857
I see the origins of it now.

39:17.362 --> 39:20.997
You're gonna roll over
and take Pete's side.

39:20.999 --> 39:24.700
You mean my son's side.

39:33.511 --> 39:36.979
I appreciate your understanding.

39:43.721 --> 39:50.559
July 3rd, 1863,

39:50.561 --> 39:55.264
against the advice of
Lieutenant-General Longstreet,

39:55.266 --> 39:58.534
General Lee charged his men

39:58.536 --> 40:01.704
across the open fields of Gettysburg...

40:04.274 --> 40:09.277
...sealing the tragic
fate of the Confederacy.

40:09.279 --> 40:15.283
Now, why didn't he just move
around the Federal right flank

40:15.285 --> 40:19.688
and force them Yankee
dogs out of position?

40:21.058 --> 40:24.893
I guess we will never know.

40:27.698 --> 40:31.433
Even the greatest generals
are not immune to error.

40:35.872 --> 40:38.806
You really do need a break.

